Yes: we can watch the page for **newly-added menu cards** and tag them automatically, while caching the GraphQL results so we don’t keep re-fetching the same menuItemIds.

Below is a drop-in replacement script. Paste it in the console on the menu page and hit Enter.

### What it does

- Tags all **currently visible** items (like before).
- Sets up a **MutationObserver** on `document.body`.
- Whenever new `data-cy="menu_item_card"` nodes are added (from scrolling / lazy load), it:
  - Extracts `menuItemId` from `id="NNNNN-menu-item"`.
  - Uses a **cache** of `dish.modifierGroups` (with min/max) per menuItemId.
  - Adds the tags (with hover tooltip for min/max) to the new card.

You can stop it later with `window.modTagsObserver.disconnect()` if you want.

